Template: rws2811/enable-spi
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Enable SPI on this Raspberry Pi?
 The WS2811 LED controller requires the SPI interface to be enabled.
 This will add 'dtparam=spi=on' to /boot/firmware/config.txt and
 the change will take effect on the next reboot.

Template: rws2811/buffer-size
Type: string
Default: 150
Description: Frame buffer size in bytes:
 Number of bytes per LED frame. This should match the number of LEDs
 multiplied by the bytes per LED (e.g. 50 LEDs * 3 bytes = 150).
 The value must fit within a single UDP packet (max 1472 for MTU 1500).

Template: rws2811/spi-speed
Type: string
Default: 2000000
Description: SPI speed in Hz:
 Clock speed for the SPI bus.

Template: rws2811/spi-device
Type: string
Default: /dev/spidev0.0
Description: SPI device path:
 Path to the SPI device node.

Template: rws2811/frame-rate
Type: string
Default: 60
Description: Frame rate in FPS:
 How often to send the frame buffer to the SPI device.

Template: rws2811/listen-address
Type: string
Default: 0.0.0.0:1337
Description: UDP listen address:
 Address and port to listen for incoming LED frames.
